# Copy to .env and fill.
#
# Default LLM for this repo’s EC2 track (NGC): 
#   nvcr.io/nim/meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct:2.0.3
# Set OPENAI_MODEL to the exact "id" from: curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/models
#
# Session 1 (OpenAI-compatible NIM / Ollama / OpenAI):
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=not-used
# OPENAI_MODEL=meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct
#
# NIM/vLLM: many images reject tool_choice=auto unless the server is started with
# --enable-auto-tool-choice and --tool-call-parser. Session 1 strips tool_choice by
# default (tools still work). To send tool_choice (e.g. OpenAI API), set:
#   OPENAI_STRIP_TOOL_CHOICE=0
# If something sets OPENAI_STRIP_TOOL_CHOICE=0 but you still hit vLLM's "auto tool
# choice" error, force stripping: SESSION1_FORCE_STRIP_TOOL_CHOICE=1
#
# Session 1 also patches openai's chat.completions.create (process-wide after first
# LLM build). Set OPENAI_STRIP_TOOL_CHOICE=0 to disable stripping entirely.
#
# NIM/vLLM: if you see 400 "only supports single tool-calls at once", Session 1 already
# sends parallel_tool_calls=false by default. To allow parallel tool calls (OpenAI API):
#   SESSION1_PARALLEL_TOOL_CALLS=1
# (alias: OPENAI_PARALLEL_TOOL_CALLS)
#
# Get OPENAI_MODEL from: curl -s OPENAI_BASE_URL/../models or /v1/models depending on server.

# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
# OPENAI_MODEL=llama3.2:3b
